column10: Testosterone Cypionate is a long-acting form of testosterone, the primary male sex hormone. It's used in hormone replacement therapy (HRT) to treat low testosterone levels in adult men (and sometimes women) to help improve mood, energy, libido, muscle mass, fat distribution, and overall quality of life. It's administered via intramuscular injection, typically once every 7–10 days.
